â”œâ”€â”€ requirements.txt       # Python dependencies
â””â”€â”€ README.md              # Project documentation
```

## ğŸ”§ Features

- ğŸ” Detects circular regions (main body of the component)
- ğŸŸ¢ Fits ellipses to small protrusions ("legs") around the circle
- ğŸ¯ Filters using area, aspect ratio, and angle to identify valid legs
- ğŸ–¼ï¸ Visualizes all detected legs with **green ellipses** on the original image

## ğŸ› ï¸ Setup Instructions

### 1. Open the project folder in VS code

### 2. Create a Virtual Environment (Recommended)
```bash
python -m venv .venv
.\.venv\Scripts\activate   # On Windows
